article.headline: Mount St. Mary's 77, Quinnipiac 73
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Shivaughn Wiggins led Mount St. Mary's with 17 points as they held on to beat Quinnipiac 77-73 Wednesday night in Northeast Conference play. Rashad Whack and Julian Norfleet each scored 13 points to help Mount St. Mary's (8-12, 3-6) snap a two-game skid. Trailing 56-43 with 12:59 left, Quinnipiac fought back to get within two, 71-69, with just over a minute remaining in the game. After Whack made three free throws, extending the Mountaineers' lead to 74-69 with 31 seconds left, the Bobcats' Dave Johnson made a 3-pointer to make it 74-72 with 17 seconds to play. Ike Azotam made a free throw for Quinnipiac (8-13, 4-5) with 11 seconds left to get within one, 74-73, but the Bobcats failed to score again while the Mountaineers sealed the victory with three free throws in the final four seconds. Quinnipiac's Ousmane Drame finished with career-highs of 19 points and 20 rebounds.
